.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In general, studies on subsidized inputs in the health sector focus most
 on intended use as the primary outcome.
 In our case, intended use is considered an intermediary outcome; we are
 most interested in the learning that emanates from the (subsidized) seed
 pack as evidenced by subsequent adoption of the seed in the next year when
 the seed is not subsidized anymore.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
